# Card-audit (mtg-948 Part B): Sinkhole — destroy target land (scripted).
#
# Closed issue mtg-542 closed Sinkhole as WORKING but carried NO scripted puzzle
# with semantic assertions (the pre-existing sinkhole_destroys_land.pzl is an
# old golden-log-only puzzle with no [assertions] section and relies on the
# heuristic AI to pick the target). This audit puzzle SCRIPTS the cast and
# asserts the outcome.
#
# Sinkhole is a {B}{B} sorcery: "Destroy target land." (CR 701.7 destroy -> put
# into owner's graveyard).
#
# Aspects exercised (issue mtg-542):
#   1. Parses + castable as a {B}{B} sorcery (spell cast assertion).
#   2. Land-restricted targeting (ValidTgts$ Land) resolves to a land.
#   3. Destroy effect moves the targeted land battlefield -> owner's graveyard.
#
# Scenario:
#   - P0: Sinkhole in hand, 2 Swamps to pay {B}{B}.
#   - P1: a single Plains on the battlefield (the only legal land target whose
#     name is unambiguous — P0's lands are Swamps, so `targeting Plains` picks
#     P1's land, not P0's).
#   - Script: P0 casts Sinkhole at the Plains; it is destroyed into P1's graveyard.

[metadata]
Name:Card Audit - Sinkhole Destroys a Land
Goal:Win
Turns:1
Difficulty:Easy
Description:P0 scripts Sinkhole ({B}{B} sorcery) at P1's Plains, destroying it. The land moves from P1's battlefield to P1's graveyard. Backs issue mtg-542 (Destroy over ValidTgts$ Land; CR 701.7).

[state]
turn=1
activeplayer=p0
activephase=MAIN1
p0life=20
p0hand=Sinkhole
p0battlefield=Swamp;Swamp
p0library=Swamp;Swamp;Swamp;Swamp;Swamp

p1life=20
p1battlefield=Plains
p1library=Mountain;Mountain;Mountain;Mountain;Mountain

[p0_script]
# Destroy P1's only Plains. The name selector is unambiguous: P0 pays with
# Swamps, so the only Plains on the board belongs to P1.
cast Sinkhole targeting Plains

[assertions]
# The land-destruction spell was actually cast by the script.
spell cast Sinkhole
# The destroyed Plains is now in its owner's (P1's) graveyard. Assertions are
# evaluated on the FINAL game state; a destroyed permanent stays in the
# graveyard, so this is a stable end-state check.
opponent graveyard contains Plains
